name: Afterlife
text: Destroy target creature. It can't be regenerated. Its controller puts a 1/1 white Spirit creature token with flying onto the battlefield.

name: Alabaster Wall
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{T}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.
flavor: Its mortar is mixed with waters straight from the Fountain of Cho.

name: Armistice
text: {3}{W}{W}: You draw a card and target opponent gains 3 life.
flavor: We all must profit for peace to last.\n—Mercadian saying

name: Arrest
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature can't attack or block, and its activated abilities can't be activated.
flavor: Orim had no memory of the previous night—the first thing she could remember was waking up with the dead guard's blood on her hands.

name: Ballista Squad
text: {X}{W}, {T}: Ballista Squad deals X damage to target attacking or blocking creature.
flavor: The perfect antidote for a tightly packed formation.

name: Charm Peddler
text: {W}, {T}, Discard a card: The next time a source of your choice would deal damage to target creature this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Charmed Griffin
text: Flying\nWhen Charmed Griffin enters the battlefield, each other player may put an artifact or enchantment card onto the battlefield from his or her hand.
flavor: Are you sure you can afford such a luxury?

name: Cho-Arrim Alchemist
text: {1}{W}{W}, {T}, Discard a card: The next time a source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage. You gain life equal to the damage prevented this way.

name: Cho-Arrim Bruiser
text: Whenever Cho-Arrim Bruiser attacks, you may tap up to two target creatures.
flavor: He doesn't know why the Cho-Arrim fight the Mercadians, but he's happy to bash heads for them anyway.

name: Cho-Arrim Legate
text: Protection from black\nIf an opponent controls a Swamp and you control a Plains, you may cast Cho-Arrim Legate without paying its mana cost.

name: Cho-Manno, Revolutionary
text: Prevent all damage that would be dealt to Cho-Manno, Revolutionary.
flavor: "Mercadia's masks can no longer hide the truth. Our day has come at last."\n—Cho-Manno

name: Cho-Manno's Blessing
text:
Flash
Enchant creature
As Cho-Manno's Blessing enters the battlefield, choose a color.
Enchanted creature has protection from the chosen color. This effect doesn't remove Cho-Manno's Blessing.

name: Common Cause
text: Nonartifact creatures get +2/+2 as long as they all share a color.
flavor: Mercadia City's troops are at their best when they have no enemy to fight.

name: Cornered Market
text: Players can't cast spells with the same name as a nontoken permanent.\nPlayers can't play nonbasic lands with the same name as a nontoken permanent.
flavor: Don't step on the livelihood of other vendors, or they may step on you.\n—Mercadian saying

name: Crackdown
text: Nonwhite creatures with power 3 or greater don't untap during their controllers' untap steps.
flavor: "There is no place for mercy in defense of our lives."\n—Ta-Spon, Cho-Arrim executioner

name: Crossbow Infantry
text: {T}: Crossbow Infantry deals 1 damage to target attacking or blocking creature.
flavor: The crossbow is the ideal weapon for the lazy Mercadians: just point and shoot.

name: Devout Witness
text: {1}{W}, {T}, Discard a card: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: The Cho-Arrim fought Mercadia's decadence with more than just swords.

name: Disenchant
text: Destroy target artifact or enchantment.
flavor: The scepter of power is fragile in a calloused hand.\n—Cho-Arrim saying

name: Fountain Watch
text: Artifacts and enchantments you control have shroud. (They can't be the targets of spells or abilities.)
flavor: The Cho-Arrim didn't rely only on a secret location to protect their Fountain.

name: Fresh Volunteers
flavor: Every Cho-Arrim villager is a potential warrior; when they are called, they abandon their peaceful way of life and take up arms to defend it.

name: Honor the Fallen
text: Exile all creature cards from all graveyards. You gain 1 life for each card exiled this way.
flavor: "May the River claim Cho-Manno's body, wherever it lies."\n—Ta-Karnst, Cho-Arrim healer

name: Ignoble Soldier
text: Whenever Ignoble Soldier becomes blocked, prevent all combat damage that would be dealt by it this turn.
flavor: Cowardice is a term invented by those with no cunning.

name: Inviolability
text: Enchant creature\nPrevent all damage that would be dealt to enchanted creature.
flavor: A soldier's faith is magic strong enough to protect against any blade.

name: Ivory Mask
text: You have shroud. (You can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
flavor: "I did not choose my role, Orim," said Cho-Manno patiently, "and I suspect Gerrard did not choose his."

name: Jhovall Queen
text: Vigilance
flavor: War-trained jhovalls eat twice their weight in war-trained soldiers daily.

name: Jhovall Rider
text: Trample
flavor: Don't be fooled by the riders' fluid grace—it takes years of practice to ride these beasts.

name: Last Breath
text: Exile target creature with power 2 or less. Its controller gains 4 life.
flavor: "The River flows. My soul returns."

name: Moment of Silence
text: Target player skips his or her next combat phase this turn.
flavor: The silence commemorates not those who've died, but those about to.

name: Moonlit Wake
text: Whenever a creature dies, you gain 1 life.
flavor: "As long as Rushwood glows, no life is ever truly lost."\n—Ta-Karnst, Cho-Arrim healer

name: Muzzle
text: Enchant creature\nPrevent all damage that would be dealt by enchanted creature.
flavor: Clenched teeth do not bite.\n—Cho-Arrim saying

name: Nightwind Glider
text: Flying, protection from black
flavor: Once you learn to float on the shadows, you'll never fear them again.

name: Noble Purpose
text: Whenever a creature you control deals combat damage, you gain that much life.
flavor: Fighting for the right reason is itself a source of strength.

name: Orim's Cure
text: If you control a Plains, you may tap an untapped creature you control rather than pay Orim's Cure's mana cost.\nPrevent the next 4 damage that would be dealt to target creature or player this turn.

name: Pious Warrior
text: Whenever Pious Warrior is dealt combat damage, you gain that much life.
flavor: The Cho-Arrim make no distinction between healers and soldiers.

name: Ramosian Captain
text: First strike\n{5}, {T}: Search your library for a Rebel permanent card with converted mana cost 4 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: The Cho-Arrim believe in leading by example.

name: Ramosian Commander
text: {6}, {T}: Search your library for a Rebel permanent card with converted mana cost 5 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: "Cho-Manno guides your spirit. I guide your sword."

name: Ramosian Lieutenant
text: {4}, {T}: Search your library for a Rebel permanent card with converted mana cost 3 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: "Give me your hand and I will give you victory."

name: Ramosian Rally
text: If you control a Plains, you may tap an untapped creature you control rather than pay Ramosian Rally's mana cost.\nCreatures you control get +1/+1 until end of turn.

name: Ramosian Sergeant
text: {3}, {T}: Search your library for a Rebel permanent card with converted mana cost 2 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Her commands are part rallying cry, part sermon, and wholly undeniable.

name: Ramosian Sky Marshal
text: Flying\n{7}, {T}: Search your library for a Rebel permanent card with converted mana cost 6 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: The Cho-Arrim fell from the sky onto Mercadia City like a vengeful rain.

name: Rappelling Scouts
text: Flying\n{2}{W}: Rappelling Scouts gains protection from the color of your choice until end of turn.

name: Renounce
text: Sacrifice any number of permanents. You gain 2 life for each permanent sacrificed this way.
flavor: Gerrard offered no defense to Orim's condemnation; the mission was under his command, and he was responsible.

name: Revered Elder
text: {1}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt to Revered Elder this turn.
flavor: The Cho-Arrim worship life and revere those who've experienced it longest.

name: Reverent Mantra
text: You may exile a white card from your hand rather than pay Reverent Mantra's mana cost.\nChoose a color. All creatures gain protection from the chosen color until end of turn.

name: Righteous Aura
text: {W}, Pay 2 life: The next time a source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.
flavor: "There is a great difference between pain and injury."\n—Cho-Manno

name: Righteous Indignation
text: Whenever a creature blocks a black or red creature, the blocking creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "You are the disease that plagues Mercadia. I am the healer's knife that will cut you out."

name: Security Detail
text: {W}{W}: Put a 1/1 white Soldier creature token onto the battlefield. Activate this ability only if you control no creatures and only once each turn.

name: Soothing Balm
text: Target player gains 5 life.
flavor: Orim taught Ta-Karnst and the other Cho-Arrim healers a far less invasive method of healing.

name: Spiritual Focus
text: Whenever a spell or ability an opponent controls causes you to discard a card, you gain 2 life and you may draw a card.

name: Steadfast Guard
text: Vigilance (Attacking doesn't cause this creature to tap.)
flavor: The Mercadians were prepared for the guard, but the guard was even more prepared for the Mercadians.

name: Story Circle
text: As Story Circle enters the battlefield, choose a color.\n{W}: The next time a source of your choice of the chosen color would deal damage to you this turn, prevent that damage.

name: Task Force
text: Whenever Task Force becomes the target of a spell or ability, it gets +0/+3 until end of turn.
flavor: They are the reflection of Rushwood's glow on the edge of a wooden sword.

name: Thermal Glider
text: Flying, protection from red
flavor: "The Mercadians are too busy looking down on us to see us coming."\n—Cho-Arrim rebel

name: Tonic Peddler
text: {W}, {T}, Discard a card: Target player gains 3 life.
flavor: "The price is written at the bottom of the cup."

name: Trap Runner
text: {T}: Target unblocked attacking creature becomes blocked. Activate this ability only during combat after blockers are declared. (This ability works on creatures that can't be blocked.)
flavor: "How could I catch her when the trees conspired to stop me?"

name: Wave of Reckoning
text: Each creature deals damage to itself equal to its power.
flavor: Inner conflict can defeat a soldier more quickly than any army.

name: Wishmonger
text: {2}: Target creature gains protection from the color of its controller's choice until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.
flavor: "It's not what you ask for, but how you ask for it."

name: Aerial Caravan
text: Flying\n{1}{U}{U}: Exile the top card of your library. Until end of turn, you may play that card. (Reveal the card as you exile it.)
flavor: Successful delivery is not guaranteed.

name: Balloon Peddler
text: {U}, {T}, Discard a card: Target creature gains flying until end of turn.
flavor: The market festival turned out to be the high point of Jaffy's visit.

name: Blockade Runner
text: {U}: Blockade Runner can't be blocked this turn.
flavor: "I need to get back to Mercadia City," said Sisay. "We can get you there," the vizier answered. "Easily."

name: Brainstorm
text: Draw three cards, then put two cards from your hand on top of your library in any order.
flavor: "I see more than others do because I know where to look."\n—Saprazzan vizier

name: Bribery
text: Search target opponent's library for a creature card and put that card onto the battlefield under your control. Then that player shuffles his or her library.
flavor: In Mercadia City, loyalties extend only as far as your purse can stretch.

name: Buoyancy
text: Flash\nEnchant creature\nEnchanted creature has flying.
flavor: Saprazzan merfolk become legged on land, but some find it quicker to bring the water with them.

name: Chambered Nautilus
text: Whenever Chambered Nautilus becomes blocked, you may draw a card.
flavor: What's merely a home for the nautilus can become exquisite jewelry in the hands of Saprazzan artisans.

name: Chameleon Spirit
text: As Chameleon Spirit enters the battlefield, choose a color.\nChameleon Spirit's power and toughness are each equal to the number of permanents of the chosen color your opponents control.

name: Charisma
text: Enchant creature\nWhenever enchanted creature deals damage to a creature, gain control of the other creature for as long as Charisma remains on the battlefield.
flavor: It was Gerrard's nature to lead and the Mercadians' to follow.

name: Cloud Sprite
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nCloud Sprite can block only creatures with flying.
flavor: The delicate sprites carry messages for Saprazzans, but they refuse to land in Mercadia City's filthy markets.

name: Coastal Piracy
text: Whenever a creature you control deals combat damage to an opponent, you may draw a card.
flavor: "I don't like to think of myself as a pirate. I'm more like a stimulator of the local economy."

name: Counterspell
text: Counter target spell.
flavor: "Your attack has been rendered harmless. It is, however, quite pretty."\n—Saprazzan vizier

name: Cowardice
text: Whenever a creature becomes the target of a spell or ability, return that creature to its owner's hand. (It won't be affected by the spell or ability.)
flavor: Gerrard was the Mercadian soldiers' greatest hero; they followed him blindly. When he left, they stumbled around blindly.

name: Customs Depot
text: Whenever you cast a creature spell, you may pay {1}. If you do, draw a card, then discard a card.
flavor: A bribe is always faster than filling out paperwork.

name: Darting Merfolk
text: {U}: Return Darting Merfolk to its owner's hand.
flavor: You might as well try to catch water with a net.

name: Dehydration
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nEnchanted creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step.
flavor: "You say Saprazzo is a city built on water? I hope they have enough to wash the dust from my throat."\n—Sisay

name: Diplomatic Escort
text: {U}, {T}, Discard a card: Counter target spell or ability that targets a creature.

name: Diplomatic Immunity
text: Enchant creature\nShroud (A permanent with shroud can't be the target of spells or abilities.)\nEnchanted creature has shroud.

name: Drake Hatchling
text: Flying\n{U}: Drake Hatchling gets +1/+0 until end of turn. Activate this ability only once each turn.
flavor: There is beauty in the space between learning to fly and taking it for granted.

name: Embargo
text: Nonland permanents don't untap during their controllers' untap steps.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you lose 2 life.

name: Energy Flux
text: All artifacts have "At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice this artifact unless you pay {2}."
flavor: Karn said nothing—he just grasped the powerstone and squeezed tightly. The wild flashing ceased.

name: Extravagant Spirit
text: Flying\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice Extravagant Spirit unless you pay {1} for each card in your hand.
flavor: The fewer your possessions, the fewer your worries.

name: False Demise
text: Enchant creature\nWhen enchanted creature dies, return that card to the battlefield under your control.
flavor: "Go down there and fish him out. Maybe his hide will fetch a price."

name: Glowing Anemone
text: When Glowing Anemone enters the battlefield, you may return target land to its owner's hand.
flavor: Beautiful to behold, terrible to be held.

name: Gush
text: You may return two Islands you control to their owner's hand rather than pay Gush's mana cost.\nDraw two cards.
flavor: Don't trust your secrets to the sea.

name: High Seas
text: Red creature spells and green creature spells cost {1} more to cast.
flavor: Bend as the wave breaks or it will break you as well.\n—Saprazzan saying

name: Hoodwink
text: Return target artifact, enchantment, or land to its owner's hand.
flavor: The youths of Rishada's marketplace are always ready for a quick footrace.

name: Indentured Djinn
text: Flying\nWhen Indentured Djinn enters the battlefield, each other player may draw up to three cards.
flavor: It's not always clear who's the master and who's the servant.

name: Karn's Touch
text: Target noncreature artifact becomes an artifact creature with power and toughness each equal to its converted mana cost until end of turn. (It retains its abilities.)

name: Misdirection
text: You may exile a blue card from your hand rather than pay Misdirection's mana cost.\nChange the target of target spell with a single target.

name: Misstep
text: Creatures target player controls don't untap during that player's next untap step.
flavor: The feet have no eyes.\n—Saprazzan saying

name: Overtaker
text: {3}{U}, {T}, Discard a card: Untap target creature and gain control of it until end of turn. That creature gains haste until end of turn.
flavor: "It's no challenge to master a Mercadian."

name: Port Inspector
text: Whenever Port Inspector becomes blocked, you may look at defending player's hand.
flavor: "There may be a few minor additional fees, levies, duties, surtaxes, tariffs, imposts, tolls . . . ."

name: Rishadan Airship
text: Flying\nRishadan Airship can block only creatures with flying.
flavor: The view is truly spectacular—as long as you don't look at Rishada itself.

name: Rishadan Brigand
text: Flying\nWhen Rishadan Brigand enters the battlefield, each opponent sacrifices a permanent unless he or she pays {3}.\nRishadan Brigand can block only creatures with flying.

name: Rishadan Cutpurse
text: When Rishadan Cutpurse enters the battlefield, each opponent sacrifices a permanent unless he or she pays {1}.
flavor: The bigger the purse, the greater the fool.\n—Rishadan saying

name: Rishadan Footpad
text: When Rishadan Footpad enters the battlefield, each opponent sacrifices a permanent unless he or she pays {2}.
flavor: "The best things in life are free. Money, for instance."

name: Sailmonger
text: {2}: Target creature gains flying until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.
flavor: Clients who cheat the sailmonger make an impact on the rest.

name: Sand Squid
text: Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)\nYou may choose not to untap Sand Squid during your untap step.\n{T}: Tap target creature. That creature doesn't untap during its controller's untap step for as long as Sand Squid remains tapped.

name: Saprazzan Bailiff
text: When Saprazzan Bailiff enters the battlefield, exile all artifact and enchantment cards from all graveyards.\nWhen Saprazzan Bailiff leaves the battlefield, return all artifact and enchantment cards from all graveyards to their owners' hands.

name: Saprazzan Breaker
text: {U}: Put the top card of your library into your graveyard. If that card is a land card, Saprazzan Breaker can't be blocked this turn.

name: Saprazzan Heir
text: Whenever Saprazzan Heir becomes blocked, you may draw three cards.
flavor: Within the walls of the floating city, Saprazzan wealth is like Saprazzan water: abundant, free-flowing, and accessible to all.

name: Saprazzan Legate
text: Flying\nIf an opponent controls a Mountain and you control an Island, you may cast Saprazzan Legate without paying its mana cost.

name: Saprazzan Outrigger
text: When Saprazzan Outrigger attacks or blocks, put it on top of its owner's library at end of combat.
flavor: The Saprazzans excel at both tactics: hit and run.

name: Saprazzan Raider
text: When Saprazzan Raider becomes blocked, return it to its owner's hand.
flavor: Some quick dagger work and then back to the sea—that's the Saprazzan way.

name: Shoving Match
text: Until end of turn, all creatures gain "{T}: Tap target creature."
flavor: Rishadan barkeeps know something the Mercadians have yet to learn: if you keep pushing, someone will eventually push back.

name: Soothsaying
text: {3}{U}{U}: Shuffle your library.\n{X}: Look at the top X cards of your library, then put them back in any order.
flavor: The vizier's wisdom proved invaluable in untangling the Mercadian knot of lies.

name: Squeeze
text: Sorcery spells cost {3} more to cast.
flavor: Any pirate would prefer Rishada's swift and cruel justice to Saprazzo's patient punishments.

name: Statecraft
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt to and dealt by creatures you control.
flavor: "Inside these walls, peace; outside, sharks. You choose."\n—Saprazzan vizier

name: Stinging Barrier
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{U}, {T}: Stinging Barrier deals 1 damage to target creature or player.

name: Thwart
text: You may return three Islands you control to their owner's hand rather than pay Thwart's mana cost.\nCounter target spell.

name: Tidal Bore
text: You may return an Island you control to its owner's hand rather than pay Tidal Bore's mana cost.\nYou may tap or untap target creature.
flavor: The dry riverbed became a raging torrent, and the Cho-Arrim claimed their prize.

name: Tidal Kraken
text: Tidal Kraken can't be blocked.
flavor: To merfolk, pirates are a nuisance. To pirates, merfolk are a threat. To the kraken, they're both appetizers.

name: Timid Drake
text: Flying\nWhen another creature enters the battlefield, return Timid Drake to its owner's hand.
flavor: It flees from anything that isn't shaped like a cloud.

name: Trade Routes
text: {1}: Return target land you control to its owner's hand.\n{1}, Discard a land card: Draw a card.
flavor: Like the price of goods, the value of the routes was renegotiated daily.

name: War Tax
text: {X}{U}: This turn, creatures can't attack unless their controller pays {X} for each attacking creature he or she controls.
flavor: The worst thing about being a depraved pirate is having to work with a bunch of depraved pirates.

name: Waterfront Bouncer
text: {U}, {T}, Discard a card: Return target creature to its owner's hand.
flavor: Closing time comes earlier to some than to others.

name: Alley Grifters
text: Whenever Alley Grifters becomes blocked, defending player discards a card.
flavor: One distracts the victim, the other extracts the valuables.

name: Black Market
text: Whenever a creature dies, put a charge counter on Black Market.\nAt the beginning of your precombat main phase, add {B} to your mana pool for each charge counter on Black Market.

name: Bog Smugglers
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)
flavor: They slide over the bog like oil across glass.

name: Bog Witch
text: {B}, {T}, Discard a card: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: The world is the body. The mana is the blood. The witch is the surgeon.

name: Cackling Witch
text: {X}{B}, {T}, Discard a card: Target creature gets +X/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: The touch of his madness can drive anyone into a killing frenzy.

name: Cateran Brute
text: {2}, {T}: Search your library for a Mercenary permanent card with converted mana cost 2 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: The Cateran guild prefers to call them "public relations."

name: Cateran Enforcer
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)\n{4}, {T}: Search your library for a Mercenary permanent card with converted mana cost 4 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Cateran Kidnappers
text: {3}, {T}: Search your library for a Mercenary permanent card with converted mana cost 3 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Recruits aren't always volunteers.

name: Cateran Overlord
text: Sacrifice a creature: Regenerate Cateran Overlord.\n{6}, {T}: Search your library for a Mercenary permanent card with converted mana cost 6 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Cateran Persuader
text: {1}, {T}: Search your library for a Mercenary permanent card with converted mana cost 1 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Cateran Slaver
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)\n{5}, {T}: Search your library for a Mercenary permanent card with converted mana cost 5 or less and put it onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Cateran Summons
text: Search your library for a Mercenary card, reveal that card, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Even when recruitment is slow, the guild can always cook something up.

name: Conspiracy
text: As Conspiracy enters the battlefield, choose a creature type.\nCreature cards you own that aren't on the battlefield, creature spells you control, and creatures you control are the chosen type.

name: Corrupt Official
text: {2}{B}: Regenerate Corrupt Official.\nWhenever Corrupt Official becomes blocked, defending player discards a card at random.
flavor: His favor comes at a high price.

name: Dark Ritual
text: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.
flavor: "Eye of twilight, give us sight.\nTake our offer, give us might.\nMake our power tears of night."

name: Deathgazer
text: Whenever Deathgazer blocks or becomes blocked by a nonblack creature, destroy that creature at end of combat.

name: Deepwood Ghoul
text: Pay 2 life: Regenerate Deepwood Ghoul.
flavor: They feed on the living to stay undead.

name: Deepwood Legate
text: If an opponent controls a Forest and you control a Swamp, you may cast Deepwood Legate without paying its mana cost.\n{B}: Deepwood Legate gets +1/+1 until end of turn.

name: Delraich
text: Trample\nYou may sacrifice three black creatures rather than pay Delraich's mana cost.
flavor: It wears the souls of its victims like jewels on a chain.

name: Enslaved Horror
text: When Enslaved Horror enters the battlefield, each other player may return a creature card from his or her graveyard to the battlefield.

name: Extortion
text: Look at target player's hand and choose up to two cards from it. That player discards those cards.
flavor: The enforcers make no effort to distinguish gold from flesh.

name: Forced March
text: Destroy all creatures with converted mana cost X or less.
flavor: The Caterans call it a screening process. The dead are in no condition to argue.

name: Ghoul's Feast
text: Target creature gets +X/+0 until end of turn, where X is the number of creature cards in your graveyard.
flavor: Mercadians not wealthy enough to buy a tomb are thrown into a bog called "the Ghoul's Larder."

name: Haunted Crossroads
text: {B}: Put target creature card from your graveyard on top of your library.
flavor: It seemed as if no one wanted them to reach the Henge of Ramos—not even the dead.

name: Highway Robber
text: When Highway Robber enters the battlefield, target opponent loses 2 life and you gain 2 life.
flavor: "Tonight, madam, it's your money and your life."

name: Instigator
text: {1}{B}{B}, {T}, Discard a card: Creatures target player controls attack this turn if able.
flavor: The desecration of their dead makes even the Saprazzans careless.

name: Insubordination
text: Enchant creature\nAt the beginning of the end step of enchanted creature's controller, Insubordination deals 2 damage to that player unless that creature attacked this turn.

name: Intimidation
text: Creatures you control have fear. (They can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)
flavor: "If they move, kill them. In fact, kill one now to make sure the other understands."

name: Larceny
text: Whenever a creature you control deals combat damage to a player, that player discards a card.

name: Liability
text: Whenever a nontoken permanent is put into a player's graveyard from the battlefield, that player loses 1 life.
flavor: Gerrard realized that the helpless woman they'd rescued from Rath was nothing of the sort.

name: Maggot Therapy
text: Flash\nEnchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/-2.
flavor: "If this is the cure, I'd hate to see the disease."\n—Orim

name: Midnight Ritual
text: Exile X target creature cards from your graveyard. For each creature card exiled this way, put a 2/2 black Zombie creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: Bury old friends deeply, lest they return bearing worms.

name: Misshapen Fiend
text: Flying
flavor: You'd scarcely believe they could fly until they drop out of the sky onto you.

name: Molting Harpy
text: Flying\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice Molting Harpy unless you pay {2}.
flavor: Shed harpy feathers leave painful wounds—which explains the harpies' mood.

name: Nether Spirit
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, if Nether Spirit is the only creature card in your graveyard, you may return Nether Spirit to the battlefield.
flavor: It roams in both the worlds of the living and the dead but belongs to neither.

name: Notorious Assassin
text: {2}{B}, {T}, Discard a card: Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: He wears his infamy like a fine silk shirt.

name: Pretender's Claim
text: Enchant creature\nWhenever enchanted creature becomes blocked, tap all lands defending player controls.
flavor: The surest way to lose your holdings is to plead for them in Mercadia City's courts.

name: Primeval Shambler
text: {B}: Primeval Shambler gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: His mind, like his body, is made up of the swamp's flotsam.

name: Putrefaction
text: Whenever a player casts a green or white spell, that player discards a card.
flavor: "Do you want to be alive or whole?"\n—Ta-Karnst, Cho-Arrim healer

name: Quagmire Lamprey
text: Whenever Quagmire Lamprey becomes blocked by a creature, put a -1/-1 counter on that creature.

name: Rain of Tears
text: Destroy target land.
flavor: Mercadian elitism is reinforced daily by physical position: their neighbors are literally beneath them and are treated accordingly.

name: Rampart Crawler
text: Rampart Crawler can't be blocked by Walls.
flavor: "Not even the magistrate in his lofty tower is out of our reach."\n—Cateran overlord

name: Rouse
text: If you control a Swamp, you may pay 2 life rather than pay Rouse's mana cost.\nTarget creature gets +2/+0 until end of turn.

name: Scandalmonger
text: {2}: Target player discards a card. Any player may activate this ability but only any time he or she could cast a sorcery.
flavor: Silence costs extra. Breaking it costs extra still.

name: Sever Soul
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated. You gain life equal to its toughness.
flavor: "With the proper tools, even the Great River can be dammed."\n—Ta-Spon, Cho-Arrim executioner

name: Silent Assassin
text: {3}{B}: Destroy target blocking creature at end of combat.
flavor: She feels no need to disturb her victim's slumber.

name: Skulking Fugitive
text: When Skulking Fugitive becomes the target of a spell or ability, sacrifice it.
flavor: In the Cateran guild, being caught is a capital offense.

name: Snuff Out
text: If you control a Swamp, you may pay 4 life rather than pay Snuff Out's mana cost.\nDestroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.
flavor: Squee watched his Kyren cousins fall with a mixture of sympathy and relief.

name: Soul Channeling
text: Enchant creature\nPay 2 life: Regenerate enchanted creature.
flavor: Driven by masters more terrible than the Mercadians could imagine, the dark overseers would pay any price to keep their shipwrights working.

name: Specter's Wail
text: Target player discards a card at random.
flavor: As he gritted his teeth to focus through the pain, Tahngarth glanced at Takara. She seemed completely unaffected.

name: Strongarm Thug
text: When Strongarm Thug enters the battlefield, you may return target Mercenary card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "No, I insist—let me carry all that heavy jewelry."

name: Thrashing Wumpus
text: {B}: Thrashing Wumpus deals 1 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: Young wumpuses are malevolent and vicious—but they grow out of it.

name: Undertaker
text: {B}, {T}, Discard a card: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: The weight of death is heavy but not immovable.

name: Unmask
text: You may exile a black card from your hand rather than pay Unmask's mana cost.\nTarget player reveals his or her hand. You choose a nonland card from it. That player discards that card.

name: Unnatural Hunger
text: Enchant creature\nAt the beginning of the upkeep of enchanted creature's controller, Unnatural Hunger deals damage to that player equal to that creature's power unless he or she sacrifices another creature.

name: Vendetta
text: Destroy target nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated. You lose life equal to that creature's toughness.
flavor: Starke knew the voice was Takara's, but the venom was Volrath's.

name: Wall of Distortion
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{2}{B}, {T}: Target player discards a card. Activate this ability only any time you could cast a sorcery.
flavor: It reflects only nightmares.

name: Arms Dealer
text: {1}{R}, Sacrifice a Goblin: Arms Dealer deals 4 damage to target creature.
flavor: He has the weapons, he has the connections, and he knows the hangar's dark secret.

name: Battle Rampart
text: Defender\n{T}: Target creature gains haste until end of turn.

name: Battle Squadron
text: Flying\nBattle Squadron's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creatures you control.
flavor: The goblins made an unruly pile with military precision.

name: Blaster Mage
text: {R}, {T}, Discard a card: Destroy target Wall.
flavor: "Don't get up. I'll show myself out."

name: Blood Hound
text: Whenever you're dealt damage, you may put that many +1/+1 counters on Blood Hound.\nAt the beginning of your end step, remove all +1/+1 counters from Blood Hound.

name: Blood Oath
text: Choose a card type. Target opponent reveals his or her hand. Blood Oath deals 3 damage to that player for each card of the chosen type revealed this way. (Artifact, creature, enchantment, instant, land, planeswalker, sorcery, and tribal are card types.)

name: Brawl
text: Until end of turn, all creatures gain "{T}: This creature deals damage equal to its power to target creature."
flavor: Anything can happen when patience is scarce and wine is abundant.

name: Cave Sense
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 and has mountainwalk. (It can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)

name: Cave-In
text: You may exile a red card from your hand rather than pay Cave-In's mana cost.\nCave-In deals 2 damage to each creature and each player.
flavor: One fleet was gone; others were poised.

name: Cavern Crawler
text: Mountainwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)\n{R}: Cavern Crawler gets +1/-1 until end of turn.

name: Ceremonial Guard
text: When Ceremonial Guard attacks or blocks, destroy it at end of combat.
flavor: "These guards are the most disciplined military unit in the city. They couldn't fight their way out of a broom closet, but they've got discipline."\n—Gerrard, to Sisay

name: Cinder Elemental
text: {X}{R}, {T}, Sacrifice Cinder Elemental: Cinder Elemental deals X damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Their rage can grow to such proportions that they explode in a cloud of fire.

name: Close Quarters
text: Whenever a creature you control becomes blocked, Close Quarters deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: The Mercadians' ineptitude in close combat sometimes accidentally pays off.

name: Crag Saurian
text: Whenever a source deals damage to Crag Saurian, that source's controller gains control of Crag Saurian.
flavor: It follows the strongest leader—the one with the longest whip.

name: Crash
text: You may sacrifice a Mountain rather than pay Crash's mana cost.\nDestroy target artifact.
flavor: Gerrard shook his head as the ground rushed to meet him. "This," he thought, "is not the start I was hoping for."

name: Flailing Manticore
text: Flying, first strike\n{1}: Flailing Manticore gets +1/+1 until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.\n{1}: Flailing Manticore gets -1/-1 until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.

name: Flailing Ogre
text: {1}: Flailing Ogre gets +1/+1 until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.\n{1}: Flailing Ogre gets -1/-1 until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.

name: Flailing Soldier
text: {1}: Flailing Soldier gets +1/+1 until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.\n{1}: Flailing Soldier gets -1/-1 until end of turn. Any player may activate this ability.

name: Flaming Sword
text: Flash\nEnchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+0 and has first strike.
flavor: "It's not Talruum crystal, but I must admit—it gets the job done."\n—Tahngarth

name: Furious Assault
text: Whenever you cast a creature spell, Furious Assault deals 1 damage to target player.
flavor: "Does it burn, Saprazzan? Do you wish you had never raised arms against us?"\n—Kyren overseer

name: Gerrard's Irregulars
text: Trample, haste
flavor: Had Gerrard realized he'd end up fighting against them, he might not have trained them so well.

name: Hammer Mage
text: {X}{R}, {T}, Discard a card: Destroy all artifacts with converted mana cost X or less.
flavor: When he's holding the hammers, everything looks like a nail.

name: Hired Giant
text: When Hired Giant enters the battlefield, each other player may search his or her library for a land card and put that card onto the battlefield. Then each player who searched his or her library this way shuffles it.

name: Kris Mage
text: {R}, {T}, Discard a card: Kris Mage deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Her blade draws blood without ever touching its target.

name: Kyren Glider
text: Flying\nKyren Glider can't block.
flavor: Mercadia's Kyren goblins are the opposite of Dominarian goblins: they're smart and cowardly.

name: Kyren Legate
text: Haste\nIf an opponent controls a Plains and you control a Mountain, you may cast Kyren Legate without paying its mana cost.

name: Kyren Negotiations
text: Tap an untapped creature you control: Kyren Negotiations deals 1 damage to target player.
flavor: Kyren goblins always speak in questions and never allow wrong answers.

name: Kyren Sniper
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you may have Kyren Sniper deal 1 damage to target player.
flavor: Kyren goblins always act behind the scenes—even in battle.

name: Lava Runner
text: Haste\nWhenever Lava Runner becomes the target of a spell or ability, that spell or ability's controller sacrifices a land.

name: Lightning Hounds
text: First strike
flavor: Quick enough to avoid jhovalls when alone and fierce enough to attack them in packs, the hounds were as at home in the mountains as the Mercadians were atop theirs.

name: Lithophage
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice Lithophage unless you sacrifice a Mountain.
flavor: It's viciously territorial, destroying every creature on the mountain it has chosen to consume.

name: Lunge
text: Lunge deals 2 damage to target creature and 2 damage to target player.
flavor: Cho-Arrim righteousness was no match for Benalish combat training.

name: Magistrate's Veto
text: White creatures and blue creatures can't block.
flavor: The magistrate had been the goblins' puppet for so long that he made the right decisions with little prompting.

name: Mercadia's Downfall
text: Each attacking creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn for each nonbasic land defending player controls.
flavor: With an explosion that shook the foundation of the city, the Weatherlight burst from the underground hangar.

name: Ogre Taskmaster
text: Ogre Taskmaster can't block.
flavor: He doesn't have to be smart—his masters only ever give him one command.

name: Pulverize
text: You may sacrifice two Mountains rather than pay Pulverize's mana cost.\nDestroy all artifacts.

name: Puppet's Verdict
text: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, destroy all creatures with power 2 or less. If you lose the flip, destroy all creatures with power 3 or greater.
flavor: "What was heads again?"\n—Mercadian magistrate

name: Robber Fly
text: Flying\nWhenever Robber Fly becomes blocked, defending player discards all the cards in his or her hand, then draws that many cards.
flavor: In pursuit of the juicy fly, Squee stumbled on the hidden hangar.

name: Rock Badger
text: Mountainwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)
flavor: The Kyren goblins created most of the inverted mountain's tunnels simply by driving the beast before them.

name: Seismic Mage
text: {2}{R}, {T}, Discard a card: Destroy target land.
flavor: The ground shakes when he walks. His customers shake if they're late with his fee.

name: Shock Troops
text: Sacrifice Shock Troops: Shock Troops deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: When goblins blow themselves up, it's called stupidity. When humans do, it's called heroism.

name: Sizzle
text: Sizzle deals 3 damage to each opponent.
flavor: Explosions ripped through the ship overhead, and those unfortunate enough to be directly below scrambled to find cover.

name: Squee, Goblin Nabob
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you may return Squee, Goblin Nabob from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "General?!" Tahngarth roared. "General nuisance, maybe."

name: Stone Rain
text: Destroy target land.
flavor: The return of Ramos was foretold by devastating natural disasters and unnatural storms.

name: Tectonic Break
text: Each player sacrifices X lands.
flavor: Only the foolish and the rich build their houses where the land is thin and the ocean is near.

name: Territorial Dispute
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, sacrifice Territorial Dispute unless you sacrifice a land.\nPlayers can't play lands.
flavor: Bit by bit, Mercadia City had forced the Cho-Arrim from their ancestral lands. They would be pushed no further.

name: Thieves' Auction
text: Exile all nontoken permanents. Starting with you, each player chooses one of the exiled cards and puts it onto the battlefield tapped under his or her control. Repeat this process until all cards exiled this way have been chosen.

name: Thunderclap
text: You may sacrifice a Mountain rather than pay Thunderclap's mana cost.\nThunderclap deals 3 damage to target creature.

name: Tremor
text: Tremor deals 1 damage to each creature without flying.
flavor: Without a word, Gerrard and Sisay ran deeper into the mountain. Neither of them intended to leave Mercadia without the Weatherlight and its crew.

name: Two-Headed Dragon
text:
Flying
Menace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
Two-Headed Dragon can block an additional creature each combat.
{1}{R}: Two-Headed Dragon gets +2/+0 until end of turn.

name: Uphill Battle
text: Creatures played by your opponents enter the battlefield tapped.
flavor: Cho-Manno knew he had no choice but to ally with Gerrard. If that's what it took to free his people, he'd pay the price.

name: Volcanic Wind
text: Volcanic Wind deals X damage divided as you choose among any number of target creatures, where X is the number of creatures on the battlefield as you cast Volcanic Wind.
flavor: The Cho-Arrim call it "the fury of Ramos."

name: War Cadence
text: {X}{R}: This turn, creatures can't block unless their controller pays {X} for each blocking creature he or she controls.
flavor: The rhythm isn't a call to arms, but a signal that the goblins have made a new enemy.

name: Warmonger
text: {2}: Warmonger deals 1 damage to each creature without flying and each player. Any player may activate this ability.
flavor: Funny how money and war travel so well together.

name: Warpath
text: Warpath deals 3 damage to each blocking creature and each blocked creature.
flavor: Cho-Manno had never seen Mercadia City's forces fight so well. The magistrate must have hired a new hero.

name: Wild Jhovall
flavor: Jhovalls sharpen their claws on trees—or on Mercadians, if no trees are handy.

name: Word of Blasting
text: Destroy target Wall. It can't be regenerated. Word of Blasting deals damage equal to that Wall's converted mana cost to the Wall's controller.

name: Ancestral Mask
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2 for each other enchantment on the battlefield.
flavor: The masks, like the ancient trees they're grown from, lend strength to the dryads.

name: Bifurcate
text: Search your library for a permanent card with the same name as target nontoken creature and put that card onto the battlefield. Then shuffle your library.

name: Boa Constrictor
text: {T}: Boa Constrictor gets +3/+3 until end of turn.
flavor: Its eyes are bigger than its stomach, but its mouth is larger still.

name: Briar Patch
text: Whenever a creature attacks you, it gets -1/-0 until end of turn.
flavor: As easily as the dryads could close a fist, so could the branches and underbrush entangle.

name: Caller of the Hunt
text: As an additional cost to cast Caller of the Hunt, choose a creature type.\nCaller of the Hunt's power and toughness are each equal to the number of creatures of the chosen type on the battlefield.

name: Caustic Wasps
text: Flying\nWhenever Caustic Wasps deals combat damage to a player, you may destroy target artifact that player controls.
flavor: Even the wasp knows how to pay the magistrate his due respect.

name: Clear the Land
text: Each player reveals the top five cards of his or her library, puts all land cards revealed this way onto the battlefield tapped, and exiles the rest.

name: Collective Unconscious
text: Draw a card for each creature you control.
flavor: Gerrard knew little of Ramos, the sky god they worshiped. But he felt the power of the chant.

name: Dawnstrider
text: {G}, {T}, Discard a card: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.
flavor: Morning's mists can hide many things.

name: Deadly Insect
text: Shroud (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
flavor: With his newfound sense of self-importance, Squee set his sights on ever-bigger bugs.

name: Deepwood Drummer
text: {G}, {T}, Discard a card: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: His drums echo Deepwood's heartbeat.

name: Deepwood Elder
text: {X}{G}{G}, {T}, Discard a card: X target lands become Forests until end of turn.
flavor: They'd guarded the Henge so long that they were as attuned to the powerstones as they were to the trees.

name: Deepwood Tantiv
text: Whenever Deepwood Tantiv becomes blocked, you gain 2 life.
flavor: A single tantiv is just as dangerous as a herd.

name: Deepwood Wolverine
text: Whenever Deepwood Wolverine becomes blocked, it gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: The jhovalls are depleting its food sources, the Mercadians are eroding its home, and you're wondering why it's angry?

name: Desert Twister
text: Destroy target permanent.
flavor: The magical dust clouds Mercadian mages use to traverse the plane generate storms that devastate the surrounding terrain. But as long as the storms don't touch the mountain, the nobles simply don't care.

name: Erithizon
text: Whenever Erithizon attacks, put a +1/+1 counter on target creature of defending player's choice.
flavor: Unlike scorpions, the erithizon isn't immune to its own weaponry.

name: Ferocity
text: Enchant creature\nWhenever enchanted creature blocks or becomes blocked, you may put a +1/+1 counter on it.
flavor: "You lot go on ahead. I'll keep killing them until it sticks."\n—Tahngarth

name: Food Chain
text: Exile a creature you control: Add X mana of any one color to your mana pool, where X is the exiled creature's converted mana cost plus one. Spend this mana only to cast creature spells.

name: Foster
text: Whenever a creature you control dies, you may pay {1}. If you do, reveal cards from the top of your library until you reveal a creature card. Put that card into your hand and the rest into your graveyard.

name: Game Preserve
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, each player reveals the top card of his or her library. If all cards revealed this way are creature cards, put those cards onto the battlefield under their owners' control.

name: Giant Caterpillar
text: {G}, Sacrifice Giant Caterpillar: Put a 1/1 green Insect creature token with flying named Butterfly onto the battlefield at the beginning of the next end step.

name: Groundskeeper
text: {1}{G}: Return target basic land card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Whereas the rebels fight to defend the land, they work to renew it.

name: Horned Troll
text: {G}: Regenerate Horned Troll.
flavor: "If I says it's a troll, it's a troll. Goblins is always right in Mercadia."\n—Squee

name: Howling Wolf
text: When Howling Wolf enters the battlefield, you may search your library for up to three cards named Howling Wolf, reveal them, and put them into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.

name: Hunted Wumpus
text: When Hunted Wumpus enters the battlefield, each other player may put a creature card from his or her hand onto the battlefield.
flavor: Just one can feed a dozen people for a month.

name: Invigorate
text: If you control a Forest, rather than pay Invigorate's mana cost, you may have an opponent gain 3 life.\nTarget creature gets +4/+4 until end of turn.

name: Land Grant
text: If you have no land cards in hand, you may reveal your hand rather than pay Land Grant's mana cost.\nSearch your library for a Forest card, reveal that card, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.

name: Ley Line
text: At the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player may put a +1/+1 counter on target creature of his or her choice.
flavor: "I can feel the strength of the entire forest."\n—Gerrard

name: Lumbering Satyr
text: All creatures have forestwalk. (They can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: The satyr carves the path that all of Rushwood follows.\n—Cho-Arrim saying

name: Lure
text: Enchant creature\nAll creatures able to block enchanted creature do so.
flavor: Deepwood's reach is not long, so it invites its enemies in.

name: Megatherium
text: Trample\nWhen Megatherium enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless you pay {1} for each card in your hand.

name: Natural Affinity
text: All lands become 2/2 creatures until end of turn. They're still lands.
flavor: As long as the dryads are a part of the forest, the forest is a part of the army.

name: Pangosaur
text: Whenever a player plays a land, return Pangosaur to its owner's hand.
flavor: Only Rushwood is vast enough to swallow this creature whole.

name: Revive
text: Return target green card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: Gerrard's heart ached, recalling the living wreath Mirri laid for her dead kin. No such memorial was left for her in Rath.

name: Rushwood Dryad
text: Forestwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: Rushwood is a living jewel that reflects its dwellers' hearts.

name: Rushwood Elemental
text: Trample\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, you may put a +1/+1 counter on Rushwood Elemental.

name: Rushwood Herbalist
text: {G}, {T}, Discard a card: Regenerate target creature.
flavor: When generals gather their armies, healers gather their herbs.

name: Rushwood Legate
text: If an opponent controls an Island and you control a Forest, you may cast Rushwood Legate without paying its mana cost.

name: Saber Ants
text: Whenever Saber Ants is dealt damage, you may put that many 1/1 green Insect creature tokens onto the battlefield.
flavor: They stay on the battlefield only long enough to consume the losers.

name: Sacred Prey
text: Whenever Sacred Prey becomes blocked, you gain 1 life.
flavor: To see one is a good omen to the Cho-Arrim.

name: Silverglade Elemental
text: When Silverglade Elemental enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a Forest card and put that card onto the battlefield. If you do, shuffle your library.

name: Silverglade Pathfinder
text: {1}{G}, {T}, Discard a card: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.

name: Snake Pit
text: Whenever an opponent casts a blue or black spell, you may put a 1/1 green Snake creature token onto the battlefield.
flavor: If the ground is smooth, the way will be rough.\n—Deepwood saying

name: Snorting Gahr
text: Whenever Snorting Gahr becomes blocked, it gets +2/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: There's little advantage to surprising the gahr.

name: Spidersilk Armor
text: Creatures you control get +0/+1 and have reach. (They can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: It hardly weighs anything, but it takes all day to remove.

name: Spontaneous Generation
text: Put a 1/1 green Saproling creature token onto the battlefield for each card in your hand.
flavor: Saprolings always thrive on the ruins of others, and Mercadia ruins more than most.

name: Squall
text: Squall deals 2 damage to each creature with flying.
flavor: The air that holds them aloft can just as easily put them down.

name: Squallmonger
text: {2}: Squallmonger deals 1 damage to each creature with flying and each player. Any player may activate this ability.
flavor: "Squall, gale, hurricane—it's all a matter of size . . . and price."

name: Stamina
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has vigilance.\nSacrifice Stamina: Regenerate enchanted creature.

name: Sustenance
text: {1}, Sacrifice a land: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: Like the dryads, the forest itself willingly gives up some of its life for the sake of the future.

name: Tiger Claws
text: Flash\nEnchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 and has trample.
flavor: Cho-Arrim martial artists emulate the beasts of their home.

name: Tranquility
text: Destroy all enchantments.
flavor: Sisay had been restored to her place on the ship, the Legacy had been recovered, and the Weatherlight was sailing home to Dominaria. Gerrard focused on the debts he'd settled . . . and on those he'd soon collect.

name: Venomous Breath
text: Choose target creature. At this turn's next end of combat, destroy all creatures that blocked or were blocked by it this turn.
flavor: The dryads need neither size nor strength to defeat their enemies in battle.

name: Venomous Dragonfly
text: Flying\nWhenever Venomous Dragonfly blocks or becomes blocked by a creature, destroy that creature at end of combat.
flavor: A pretty little death is still death.

name: Vernal Equinox
text: Any player may cast creature and enchantment cards as though they had flash.

name: Vine Dryad
text: Flash\nForestwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)\nYou may exile a green card from your hand rather than pay Vine Dryad's mana cost.

name: Vine Trellis
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: "We protect our own with our own."

name: Assembly Hall
text: {4}, {T}: Reveal a creature card in your hand. Search your library for a card with the same name as that card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then shuffle your library.

name: Barbed Wire
text: At the beginning of each player's upkeep, Barbed Wire deals 1 damage to that player.\n{2}: Prevent the next 1 damage that would be dealt by Barbed Wire this turn.
flavor: A steel snake with ten thousand teeth.

name: Bargaining Table
text: {X}, {T}: Draw a card. X is the number of cards in an opponent's hand.
flavor: Although it looks like a game, business around the table is deadly serious.

name: Credit Voucher
text: {2}, {T}, Sacrifice Credit Voucher: Shuffle any number of cards from your hand into your library, then draw that many cards.

name: Crenellated Wall
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{T}: Target creature gets +0/+4 until end of turn.
flavor: Mercadian soldiers excel at finding things to stand behind.

name: Crooked Scales
text: {4}, {T}: Flip a coin. If you win the flip, destroy target creature an opponent controls. If you lose the flip, destroy target creature you control unless you pay {3} and repeat this process.

name: Crumbling Sanctuary
text: If damage would be dealt to a player, that player exiles that many cards from the top of his or her library instead.

name: Distorting Lens
text: {T}: Target permanent becomes the color of your choice until end of turn.
flavor: The magistrate seems to prefer a distorted perspective of reality.

name: Eye of Ramos
text: {T}: Add {U} to your mana pool.\nSacrifice Eye of Ramos: Add {U} to your mana pool.
flavor: Ramos wept, and there were seas.

name: General's Regalia
text: {3}: The next time a source of your choice would deal damage to you this turn, that damage is dealt to target creature you control instead.
flavor: A uniform fit for a goblin.

name: Heart of Ramos
text: {T}: Add {R} to your mana pool.\nSacrifice Heart of Ramos: Add {R} to your mana pool.
flavor: Ramos bled, and there was fire.

name: Henge Guardian
text: {2}: Henge Guardian gains trample until end of turn.
flavor: Like so many Thran relics, the wurm engine kept operating long after its creators were gone.

name: Horn of Plenty
text: Whenever a player casts a spell, he or she may pay {1}. If that player does, he or she draws a card at the beginning of the next end step.
flavor: "This horn is an exact replica of the fabled Horn of Ramos, except mine is more lavish."\n—Mercadian magistrate

name: Horn of Ramos
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\nSacrifice Horn of Ramos: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: Ramos touched, and there was life.

name: Iron Lance
text: {3}, {T}: Target creature gains first strike until end of turn.
flavor: "The only way to get Mercadians to fight on the front lines is to give them really long weapons."\n—Gerrard

name: Jeweled Torque
